{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8cad3da2-56dc-4833-85b1-2624be4d4271","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. **MSTest v3 requires .NET 6+ or .NET Framework 4.6.2+**, but your project targets:\n\n| Target | Issue |\n|--------|-------|\n| `net5.0` | ❌ Not supported — MSTest v3 requires `net6.0` or later |\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | ❌ Not supported — too old |\n| `net462` | ✅ Supported |\n\n**To migrate to MSTest v3, you'll need to:**\n\n1. **Drop or upgrade unsupported TFMs** — replace `net5.0` → `net6.0` (or `net8.0`) and remove `netcoreapp3.1`.\n2. **Update packages** — switch to `MSTest` v3 meta-package (replaces separate `TestFramework`/`TestAdapter` references).\n\nIf you must keep testing on `netcoreapp3.1` or `net5.0`, you'll need to stay on MSTest v2 for those targets or maintain separate project configurations.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8b06194d-cd42-48b1-a3e5-2bcafa5d38ec","outputTokens":258,"requestId":"23C5:34D8DE:4690B0:4BC030:6A031130"},"id":"801485d6-7921-4a50-8b65-d60c9fe90963","timestamp":"2026-05-12T11:38:31.525Z","parentId":"3e414a5c-99d4-4c40-8996-ef1ebb482298"}
